## nostr-bray

MCP server + CLI giving AI agents sovereign Nostr identities. 238 tools across 27 groups.

## Commands

- `npm run build` — compile TypeScript
- `npm test` — run all tests (vitest, 1400 tests)
- `npm run lint` — type-check (`tsc --noEmit`)

## Architecture

Entry points:
- `src/index.ts` — MCP server (config → IdentityContext → RelayPool → tools → transport)
- `src/cli.ts` — CLI wrapper (same handlers, no MCP)

Each tool group: `src/<group>/handlers.ts` (logic) + `src/<group>/tools.ts` (Zod schemas + MCP registration).
Groups: identity, social (social/dm/blossom/articles/calendar/badges/communities/groups/wiki/search/scheduled/community-NIPs), trust, relay, zap, safety, signet, vault, util, workflow, dispatch, marketplace, privacy, moderation, handler.

Core modules:
- `src/context.ts` — IdentityContext (nsec-tree root, LRU cache, zeroise, signing)
- `src/trust-context.ts` — trust signal aggregation (Signet, WoT, Dominion)
- `src/relay-pool.ts` — relay connections, SOCKS5h, Tor policy, write queue
- `src/nip65.ts` — NIP-65 relay list (signature-verified, TTL cache)
- `src/validation.ts` — shared Zod validators (hexId, relayUrl)

## Conventions

- British English (colour, initialise, behaviour)
- ESM only
- Commits: `type: description` (feat:, fix:, test:, docs:)
- No Co-Authored-By lines
- Work on branches, merge to main (semantic-release auto-publishes)

## Security Rules

- Never return private keys in tool responses
- Zeroise Buffers in `finally` blocks
- Validate all external input via `src/validation.ts`
- Use `verifyEvent()` before trusting Nostr events from relays
- Enforce Tor policy on runtime relay additions
